      {
        "question": "Can both twins be screened in one NT scan?",
        "answer": "Yes. Each baby is measured separately."
      },
      {
        "question": "What if one twin shows high NT?",
        "answer": "Cadabams may offer NIPT or CVS for definitive results."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is the scan painful?",
        "answer": "Transabdominal scans are painless; transvaginal scans may cause mild pressure."
      },
      {
        "question": "How accurate is NT screening in twins?",
        "answer": "Approximately 75–80 % detection rate—slightly lower than in singletons."
      },
      {
        "question": "Do I need a full bladder?",
        "answer": "Yes, for clearer abdominal images."
      },
      {
